# Configuring the {{ module_name_long }} {{ module_type }}

This page describes the committed configuration file for the {{ module_name_long }} {{ module_type }}. The file lives at `config/{{ module_type }}/{{ module_name }}/config.yaml` in this repository.

!!! note "Who should edit this file?"

    Workflow runners should usually leave committed config files unchanged and use `config/config.local.yaml` for machine-specific overrides when running this project directly.
    If you import this workflow as a module into a parent workflow, provide overrides from the parent workflow config instead.
    Repository developers may update this committed file and its matching schema when changing the reproducible default behavior of the module.

If you need to add [tabular configuration data](https://snakemake.readthedocs.io/en/stable/snakefiles/configuration.html#tabular-configuration) be sure that it is loaded along side this configuration in `workflow/profiles/default/config.yaml`.

This module config is validated by `workflow/Snakefile` before rule files are included, together with all other workflow config schemas.

